article.headline: SE Louisiana 66, Tulane 63
article.story: NEW ORLEANS (AP) -- Nate Lofton scored 15 points in the second half to lead Southeastern Louisiana to 66-63 victory over Tulane on Saturday night. Lofton had 17 points for the game and grabbed seven of his eight rebounds in the second half. Southeastern (5-2) led 61-51 with four minutes to go and held off a late Tulane rally. SLU had 20 offensive rebounds and just eight turnovers to the Green Wave's 15. The Lions outrebounded Tulane 46-37 to offset its 34.4 percent shooting from the field. Tulane shot 42.9 percent from the floor. Tulane (5-2) was led by Vytas Tatarunas who posted his fourth double-double of the year with 17 points and a career-high 14 rebounds. Ben Benfield scored a game-high 18 points and Quincy Davis added 10 points for the Green Wave. Tulane led at the halftime 24-22, but Southeastern took a lead 39-35 with 12:13 left in the game after Lofton scored nine straight points in the paint. Tulane pulled within three with 58 seconds to go after a rebound dunk by Tatarunas, but Southeastern clinched the game by protecting the ball and hitting enough free throws in the final minute.
